The paper deals with image recognition using machine learning techniques, specifically for recognizing historical letters carved on stone walls. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of logistic regression and convolutional neural networks, which are common machine learning techniques used in classification tasks, indicating the likelihood of the paper belonging to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and preprocessing, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with historical graffiti, which could potentially fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
